                            <comment id="12871254" author="mdennis" created="Tue, 25 May 2010 17:16:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch against -r948111&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12871333" author="gdusbabek" created="Tue, 25 May 2010 19:48:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DD.loadSchemas() requires that system tables are present.  I wish there were a better way to do this, but I can&apos;t think of one.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12871335" author="gdusbabek" created="Tue, 25 May 2010 19:50:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m going to hold off on committing this while I investigate some more.  There&apos;s got to be a better way.  Also, I want to make sure that sstableimport isn&apos;t broken in the same fundamental way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12871366" author="mdennis" created="Tue, 25 May 2010 21:29:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;let me know if there is anything I can do to help...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12871750" author="gdusbabek" created="Wed, 26 May 2010 14:23:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Matthew, can you add this same fix to SSTableImport as well as a check immediately after the DD.loadSchemas() to verify that &amp;gt;0 non-system tables are defined?  The relevant call is DD.getNonSystemTables().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12872353" author="mdennis" created="Thu, 27 May 2010 20:36:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch2 against r948964&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12872960" author="gdusbabek" created="Fri, 28 May 2010 13:06:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;committed with minor revisions.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12873278" author="hudson" created="Sat, 29 May 2010 12:45:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #449 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/449/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Cassandra/449/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    have sstable import/export load schema from local storage. Patch by Matthew Dennis, reviewed by Gary Dusbabek. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1128&quot; title=&quot;sstable2json spews because it uses DatabaseDescriptor before loadSchemas() is called&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
